<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-05-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="242" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 20437/83.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-05-11"><hi rend="italic">May 11,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Reichstag passed potash law last evening. It empowers Bundesrat to reduce
                            prices on contracts prior to December 17, 1909, so that on deliveries
                            after May 1, 1910, the prices, duty included, shall not be higher than
                            those prevailing before June 30, 1909.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hill.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>